    "headline": "KLA Corporation’s (NASDAQ:KLAC) Q1 Sales Top Estimates But Stock Drops",
    "summary": "Semiconductor manufacturing equipment maker KLA Corporation (NASDAQ:KLAC) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2026, with sales up 11.5% year on year to $3.42 billion. Guidance for next quarter’s revenue was better than expected at $3.58 billion at the midpoint, 0.6% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $9.40 per share was 2.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.",
